EVENTS:	Cost Associated with Exit or Disposal Activities	Financial Statements and Exhibits
TEXT:
ITEM: Cost Associated with Exit or Disposal Activities
ITEM: Financial Statements and Exhibits
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
Check the appropriate box below if the Form 8-K filing is intended to simultaneously satisfy the filing obligation of the registrant under any of the following provisions (see General Instruction A.2 below):
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
On July 1, 2009 Briggs & Stratton Corporation (the "Company") announced a plan to close its Jefferson and Watertown, Wisconsin manufacturing facilities in fiscal 2010. The Power Products Segment facilities currently manufacture all portable generator, home standby generator and pressure washer products marketed and sold by the company.
The Wisconsin facilities' production will be consolidated into existing United States engine and lawn and garden product facilities to optimize plant utilization and achieve better integration between engine and end product design, manufacturing and distribution.
The decision was communicated to affected employees on July 1, 2009, and it is expected that the closure of the facilities will be completed by the end of the second quarter of fiscal 2010. The Company expects to incur pre-tax charges for facility consolidation and closure costs of approximately $10.3 million consisting of $4.6 million of asset impairment costs and $5.7 million of other costs. Cash expenditures related to the closure are estimated to be approximately $4.5 million. During the fourth quarter of fiscal 2009, the Company will recognize a pre-tax $5.8 million charge composed of $4.6 million of asset impairments and approximately $1.2 million of employee related charges for severance and pension costs. The impact of the facilities' consolidation on fiscal 2010 earnings is anticipated to be minimal because the remaining $4.5 million of closure costs are projected to be offset by savings from the consolidation. In fiscal 2011, the Company estimates approximately $11.0 million of pre-tax savings from the consolidation of operations.
A copy of the press release announcing the plan to close the Wisconsin facilities is attached hereto as Exhibit 99.1 and incorporated herein by reference.
