Any past, present, or future director, officer, employee, incorporator, agent, member or stockholder or Affiliate, as such, of the Company, any Subsidiary Guarantor or the Trustee shall not have any liability for any obligations of the Company or any Subsidiary Guarantor under the Notes, the Indenture or the Subsidiary Guarantee or for any claim based on, in respect of or by reason of, such obligations or their creation. By accepting a Note, each Holder waives and releases all such liabilities. The waiver and release are part of the consideration for the issuance of the Notes.
 
