8
Income (or loss) for such period plus (b) to the extent deducted in the determination of such Consolidated Net Income (or loss), (i) Consolidated Interest Expense; (ii) federal, state, local and foreign income taxes (including franchise taxes based upon income, gross receipts type taxes imposed in lieu of income taxes and commercial activity taxes imposed in lieu of income taxes); (iii) depreciation and amortization; (iv) any non-cash losses, expenses or charges, non-cash extraordinary losses or non-cash recurring or unusual losses; and (v) any other extraordinary losses or non-recurring or unusual losses minus (c) to the extent included in the determination of such Consolidated Net Income or loss, non-cash gains, non-cash extraordinary gains and non-cash non-recurring or unusual gains;
provided
that the amounts added pursuant to item (b)(v) above shall not exceed $15,000,000 in the aggregate in any twelve-month period.
