Interest Period
 means, as to any Eurocurrency Loan, the period commencing on the Borrowing Date for such Loan, or on the Conversion/Continuation Date on which such Loan is converted into or continued as a Eurocurrency Loan, and ending on the date one, two, three or six months thereafter (or such other period as may be approved by all Lenders) as selected by the applicable Borrower in its Notice of Borrowing or Notice of Conversion/Continuation, as the case may be;
provided
that:
13
(a)    if any Interest Period would otherwise end on a day that is not a Business Day, that Interest Period shall be extended to the following Business Day unless, in the case of a Eurocurrency Loan, the result of such extension would be to carry such Interest Period into another calendar month, in which event such Interest Period shall end on the preceding Business Day;
(b)    any Interest Period pertaining to a Eurocurrency Loan that begins on the last Business Day of a calendar month (or on a day for which there is no numerically corresponding day in the calendar month at the end of such Interest Period) shall end on the last Business Day of the calendar month at the end of such Interest Period; and
(c)    no Interest Period for any Loan shall extend beyond the scheduled Maturity Date.
